description:
- Jobs Support Scheme (JSS) will be extended by seven months, until March 2021.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
- The Jobs Growth Incentive (JGI) will be launched to support hiring in growing sectors — such as biomedical sciences, financial services, ICT, public healthcare, long-term care, F&B, and manufacturing sectors.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
- The Covid-19 Support Grant (CSG), which was introduced in May, will be extended until December 2020.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
- The eligibility for the Workfare Special Payment will be widened.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#linkinbio

On Tuesday, Feb. 18, Minister of Finance Heng Swee Keat presented the 2020 Budget and introduced two special packages to provide additional support to help Singaporeans in light of the economic impact of Covid-19.

One of the special packages is the S$4 billion Stabilisation and Support package, which is meant to stabilise the economy and support Singaporean workers and businesses.

description:
On Tuesday, Feb. 18, Minister of Finance Heng Swee Keat presented the 2020 Budget and introduced two special packages to provide additional support to help Singaporeans in light of the economic impact of Covid-19.

One of the special packages is the S$4 billion Stabilisation and Support package, which is meant to stabilise the economy and support Singaporean workers and businesses.

Top photo by Li Yang on Unsplash.

This measure is part of the S$4 billion Support and Stabilisation package, put in place to address the foremost concern of helping workers retain their jobs in this period of economic uncertainty.
